posts.raw_content:
When I started seeing all of the woke Community Notes (CN) supporting Kamala Harris during the elections, I signed up to participate in Community Notes.

After almost 8 months, I received an invitation to participate...so this requires patience. One of the first things you do is create an anon account, so although linked to your X profile, your primary account is not displayed within the CN framework.

When an X user requests a CN, it appears within the CN frame, and writers are able to create a CN or an "internal NNN" (note not needed). Once a CN or NNN is loaded, it is available within the CN frame for rating. After a not has been rated by "enough raters", an X black hole weighs whether the note is published or not (simplified for brevity). Although X states that it is not a popularity contest, it does seem to be that way.

Let me tell you that the wokest of the woke are CN authors on X. There are a few of us patriots fighting the fight, but we need an army...especially now.

Every drop made by DNI Gabbard is stocked with notes with links to the past Senate reports, previous ICA, etc...completely ignoring the context of this new evidence. And the opposite is true with things like Schiff's dump on the economy and POTUS.

As a meme warrior since 2016, I believe this is one of the few places where truth can prevail...but we need help!

SIGN UP CRITERIA FOR COMMUNITY NOTES:

--You have not violated X's rules recently (typically within the last 6 months).
--Your account is at least 6 months old.
--Your account has a verified phone number from a trusted phone carrier.

Sign up at communitynotes.x.com or navigate to Community Notes section within the X app.

You start with rating--a vote on whether a note is helpful, somewhat helpful, or not helpful--and move on to note writing after a rating impact 5. This process took about a day for me, because the review and rating process is slow.

Please help if you can!
